### LOs
addLiaisonOfficer.title = Add liaison officer
addLiaisonOfficer.heading = Add liaison officer
addLiaisonOfficer.p1 = You must have at least 1 liaison officer to register your organisation as an ISA manager.
addLiaisonOfficer.p2 = You can add up to {0} liaison officers.
addLiaisonOfficer.details.summary = What is a liaison officer?
addLiaisonOfficer.details.content.p1 = Liaison officers act as a point of contact between the ISA manager and HMRC.
addLiaisonOfficer.details.content.p2 = They provide their name, telephone number and email address and are individuals an organisation appoints to provide day-to-day contact with HMRC.
addLiaisonOfficer.button = Add a liaison officer
addLiaisonOfficer.link = Return to Manage ISAs

liaisonOfficerName.title = What is the full name of the liaison officer?
liaisonOfficerName.heading = What is the full name of the liaison officer?
liaisonOfficerName.hint = You must have at least 1 liaison officer to register your organisation as an ISA manager. You can add up to {0} liaison officers.
liaisonOfficerName.error.required = Enter the full name of the liaison officer you’re adding
liaisonOfficerName.error.invalid = The full name must only include letters a to z, hyphens, spaces and apostrophes
liaisonOfficerName.checkYourAnswersLabel = Name
liaisonOfficerName.change.hidden = name of liaison officer

liaisonOfficerEmail.title = What is the email address of {0}?
liaisonOfficerEmail.heading = What is the email address of {0}?
liaisonOfficerEmail.hint = This is the email address that HMRC will use to contact the liaison officer
liaisonOfficerEmail.error.required = Enter the email address of the liaison officer you’re adding. Use a name, @ symbol and a domain name, like yourname@example.com
liaisonOfficerEmail.error.invalid = Enter an email address in the correct format, like name@example.com
liaisonOfficerEmail.checkYourAnswersLabel = Email address
liaisonOfficerEmail.change.hidden = email address

liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.title = What is {0}’s phone number?
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.heading = What is {0}’s phone number?
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.p1 = This is the phone number that HMRC will use if there is a need to contact the liaison officer.
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.hint = This can be either a UK mobile or landline number
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.error.required = Enter the phone number of the liaison officer you’re adding. Use a UK phone number, like 01642 123 456 or 07777 777 777
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.error.invalid = The phone number must not include letters a to z, hyphens or apostrophes and must be a UK phone number, like 01642 123 456 or 07777 777 777
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.error.tooLong = The phone number you have entered is too long. Enter a UK phone number, like 01642 123 456 or 07777 777 777
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.error.tooShort = The phone number you have entered is too short. Enter a UK phone number, like 01642 123 456 or 07777 777 777
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.checkYourAnswersLabel = UK phone number
liaisonOfficerPhoneNumber.change.hidden = UK phone number

