### Certificates of Authority

eligibilityToManageIsa.title = Eligibility to manage ISAs
eligibilityToManageIsa.heading = Eligibility to manage ISAs
eligibilityToManageIsa.p1 = Before you continue, you will need to make sure you have the correct information available to show which permissions your organisation holds.
eligibilityToManageIsa.p2 = You will need to know:
eligibilityToManageIsa.bullet1 = the Articles which apply to your organisation - as set out by the FCA
eligibilityToManageIsa.bullet2 = which type of financial organisation you are
eligibilityToManageIsa.linkText = Find out more about who can manage ISAs in the Applications for ISA manager status guidance

certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.title = Certificates of authority which apply to your organisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.heading = Certificates of authority which apply to your organisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.p1 = An organisation must have the FCA’s approval to offer financial services.
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.p2 = This refers to individuals or organisations who have been authorised under the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 to carry out specific regulated financial activities.
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.p3 = Your organisation needs to be:
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.li1 = authorised under section 31(1)(a) or (c), or Schedule 5 of the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.li2 = allowed to carry out one or more regulated activities specified in Articles 14, 21, 25, 36H, 37, 39G, 40, 45, 51ZA, 51ZC, 51ZE and 53
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.li3 = able to carry out activities under Article 64 when related to the above permissions
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.li4 = aware that temporary or interim permissions (under Chapter 4 of Part 8 of the 2013 Amendment Order) are not sufficient
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.li5 = able to provide relevant evidence to confirm their authorisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.label = Do the certificates and permissions described above apply to your organisation?
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.yes = Yes - you will now tell us which articles apply to your financial organisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.no = No - you need to provide further details about your financial organisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.error.required = You need to tell us if the certificates and permissions apply to your organisation. Select yes, if they do
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.checkYourAnswersLabel = Certificates of authority that apply to your organisation
certificatesOfAuthorityYesNo.change.hidden = certificates of authority

financialOrganisation.title = Financial organisation
financialOrganisation.heading = Financial organisation
financialOrganisation.p1 = We need to know which type of organisation you are.
financialOrganisation.legend = Which best describes your organisation?
financialOrganisation.hint = Select all that apply
financialOrganisation.europeanInstitution = A European institution that has a base in the UK
financialOrganisation.creditUnion = A credit union
financialOrganisation.directorSavings = The Director of Savings
financialOrganisation.buildingSociety = A building society
financialOrganisation.bank = A bank
financialOrganisation.insuranceCompany = An insurance company
financialOrganisation.incorporatedFriendlySociety = An incorporated friendly society
financialOrganisation.registeredFriendlySociety = A registered friendly society
financialOrganisation.assuranceUndertaking = An organisation that offers assurance undertaking services
financialOrganisation.checkYourAnswersLabel = What is your financial organisation?
financialOrganisation.error.required = You need to tell us which organisation type you are. Select from the options
financialOrganisation.change.hidden = financial organisation

fcaArticles.title = FCA Articles that apply to your organisation
fcaArticles.heading = FCA Articles that apply to your organisation
fcaArticles.p1 = We need to know which of the FCA Articles apply to your organisation, as set out by the Financial Service and Markets Act 2000.
fcaArticles.h2 = Which Articles apply to your organisation?
fcaArticles.hint = Select all that apply
fcaArticles.article14 = Article 14
fcaArticles.article21 = Article 21
fcaArticles.article25 = Article 25
fcaArticles.article36H = Article 36H
fcaArticles.article37 = Article 37
